Clinical Services Unit Testing Plan
Project: Hospital Management System (HMS)
Purpose: Define the unit testing strategy, scope, standards, and coverage expectations for the Clinical Services module.
1. Overview
This document outlines the unit testing plan for the Clinical Services domain of the Hospital Management System. The goal is to ensure reliability, correctness, maintainability, and patient safety for all clinical workflows.
The Clinical Services module includes:
Patient encounters
Clinical notes
Diagnoses
Prescriptions
Medication administration
Lab orders/results
Vital signs
Allergies
Care plans
Procedures
Referrals
Clinical decision support
Discharge summaries
2. Objectives
The unit testing strategy aims to:
Validate business logic correctness
Prevent regressions
Ensure patient safety rules are enforced
Verify authorization and access control behavior
Validate edge cases and failure handling
Maintain high code quality and confidence in deployments
3. Scope
Included
Unit tests for:
Services
Domain logic
Validators
Mappers
Utility classes
Clinical rule engines
Calculation helpers
Repository abstractions (mocked dependencies)
Excluded
The following are out of scope for unit testing:
Full database integration
UI testing
End-to-end workflows
Performance testing
Security penetration testing
Third-party API availability
These will be covered by integration, system, and UAT testing phases.
4. Testing Frameworks
Recommended Stack
Layer	Recommended Tool
Unit Test Framework	JUnit 5 / NUnit / pytest
Mocking	Mockito / Moq / unittest.mock
Assertions	AssertJ / FluentAssertions
Coverage	JaCoCo / Coverlet / pytest-cov
CI Execution	GitHub Actions / GitLab CI / Jenkins
5. Test Structure Standards
Naming Convention
should_<expected_behavior>_when_<condition>
Examples:
should_create_prescription_when_valid_medication_provided
should_reject_order_when_patient_is_discharged
should_throw_exception_when_allergy_conflict_detected
6. General Unit Testing Principles
Tests must be isolated
No real database connections
No external network calls
Use mocks/stubs for dependencies
Each test should validate one behavior
Tests must be deterministic and repeatable
Avoid shared mutable state
Maintain fast execution time
7. Coverage Targets
Component	Minimum Coverage
Clinical Services	90%
Validators	95%
Critical Patient Safety Logic	100%
Utility Functions	85%
